# Trinity Re-Architecture & Colab Bridge Plan

Goal: Decouple "Trinity" logic from ad-hoc notebooks into a production-grade Python repository structure, allowing VS Code to act as the primary interface for a Colab remote runtime.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This re-architecture involves:
> 1. Moving all existing logic from `scripts/` to a structured `phases/` package in a new [trinity/](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/scripts/local_rag_builder.py#324-424) directory.
> 2. Switching from [.ipynb](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/JUDGEGUARD_SHOWCASE.ipynb) only research to "Module-first" execution.
> 3. Setting up **VS Code Remote Tunnels** in Colab for a unified development experience.

## Proposed Structure

```text
trinity/
  phases/
    __init__.py
    phase1_ingestion.py   # Colab Bridge + Gemini Audit
    phase2_rag.py         # 70/30 Hybrid Query
    phase3_sota_ast.py    # SOTA Engine (AST + MD5 Versioning)
    phase4_security.py    # JudgeGuard v3.2 + Audit
    phase5_deploy.py      # DDP Scaling + Monitoring
  config/
    trinity_config.yaml
    security_policies.yaml
  notebooks/
    trinity_colab_runtime.ipynb
```

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Import and run `phase1_ingestion` in a mocked environment.
- Verify AST extraction via `phase3_sota_ast` on sample code blocks.

### Manual Verification
- Execute `trinity_colab_runtime.ipynb` in Google Colab to verify the Remote Tunnel connection.
